01/07/2010
NICOSIA, Cyprus -- Police announced on Wednesday (June 30th) that a suspected Russian spy, who was arrested at the Larnaca airport earlier this week, has gone missing after being released on bail.
Robert Christopher Metsos, 55, was detained after Interpol alerted local authorities that he was one of 11 suspected Russian spies in the United States.
He was released on a $20,000 bail and was ordered to report to police every evening.
(Reuters, CNN, AP - 30/06/10)
